{"word":"H1241 - בָּקָר - bâqâr - baw-kawr' - Beeve","slug":"H1241","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּקָר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâqâr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-kawr'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beeve"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05E7;&#x05E8; - ba&#x0302;qa&#x0302;r</b> - <i>baw-kawr'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H1239\">H1239</a>; a <i>beeve</i> or animal of the ox kind of either gender (as used for <i>ploughing</i>); collectively a <i>herd: - </i>beeve, bull (+ -ock), + calf, + cow, great [cattle], + heifer, herd, kine, ox."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1239\">H1239</a>, <a href=\"#/H1242\">H1242</a>, <a href=\"#/H1243\">H1243</a>, <a href=\"#/H1244\">H1244</a>, <a href=\"#/H951\">H951</a>"}]}